description:
## Overview

Introduce a **Memory Qualification Layer** inside `agent-plugin-mulch` that scores, deduplicates, and filters `pendingMulchLessons` before they are written to `.mulch/candidates.jsonl`.

This reduces candidate noise by an estimated 40–70%, improving human review quality and long-term memory integrity.

---

## Architecture Fit

This feature lives **entirely within existing packages** — no new package required.

| Concern | Location |
|---|---|
| New scoring fields on `MulchLesson` | `packages/agent-types/src/lib/agent-types.ts` (additive, optional) |
| Qualifier, scorer, deduplicator | `packages/agent-plugin-mulch/src/lib/qualifier/` (new subfolder) |
| Integration | `packages/agent-plugin-mulch/src/lib/hooks.ts` (onSessionEnd only) |

---

## Step 1 — Extend MulchLesson in agent-types (non-breaking)

Add optional enrichment fields to `MulchLesson`. All are optional so existing lessons and writers remain valid:

```ts
export interface MulchLesson {
  // ... existing fields unchanged ...
  confidence?: number;        // 0–1, agent-assigned certainty
  frequency?: number;         // 1–5, how often this pattern was observed
  severity?: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high'; // impact level
}
```

> NOTE: Agents do not currently populate these fields. The scorer must degrade gracefully to defaults when they are absent.

---

## Step 2 — Add qualifier subfolder inside agent-plugin-mulch

```
packages/agent-plugin-mulch/src/lib/qualifier/
  memory-qualifier.ts
  scoring.ts
  dedupe.ts
  index.ts
```

### memory-qualifier.ts

```ts
import type { MulchLesson } from '@conscius/agent-types';
import { scoreLesson } from './scoring.js';
import { isDuplicateLesson } from './dedupe.js';

export class DefaultMemoryQualifier {
  constructor(private existingLessons: MulchLesson[] = []) {}

  accept(lesson: MulchLesson): boolean {
    if (this.score(lesson) < 0.6) return false;
    if (isDuplicateLesson(lesson, this.existingLessons)) return false;
    if (!this.isGeneralisable(lesson)) return false;
    return true;
  }

  score(lesson: MulchLesson): number {
    return scoreLesson(lesson);
  }

  private isGeneralisable(lesson: MulchLesson): boolean {
    return lesson.summary.length > 10 && lesson.recommendation.length > 20;
  }
}
```

> Note: generalisation check uses `summary` + `recommendation` (existing fields), not `pattern` (which does not exist in MulchLesson).

### scoring.ts

Scores degrade gracefully when optional fields are absent:

```ts
import type { MulchLesson } from '@conscius/agent-types';

export function scoreLesson(lesson: MulchLesson): number {
  const frequency = normalise(lesson.frequency ?? 1, 1, 5);
  const severity = mapSeverity(lesson.severity);
  const confidence = lesson.confidence ?? 0.5;
  // Use classification as a proxy for generalisation quality
  const durability = mapClassification(lesson.classification);
  return average([frequency, severity, confidence, durability]);
}

function mapSeverity(sev?: string): number {
  switch (sev) {
    case 'high': return 1;
    case 'medium': return 0.7;
    case 'low': return 0.4;
    default: return 0.5;
  }
}

function mapClassification(cls?: string): number {
  switch (cls) {
    case 'foundational': return 1;
    case 'tactical': return 0.7;
    case 'observational': return 0.4;
    default: return 0.5;
  }
}

function normalise(value: number, min: number, max: number): number {
  return Math.min(1, Math.max(0, (value - min) / (max - min)));
}

function average(values: number[]): number {
  return values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / values.length;
}
```

> Note: `classification` replaces the proposed `pattern.length` heuristic — it is a real existing field that proxies durability intent.

### dedupe.ts

Word-overlap similarity against existing lessons. Acceptable for MVP; embedding-based dedup is a future extension.

```ts
import type { MulchLesson } from '@conscius/agent-types';

export function isDuplicateLesson(
  lesson: MulchLesson,
  existing: MulchLesson[]
): boolean {
  return existing.some(
    (e) =>
      wordSimilarity(e.summary, lesson.summary) > 0.85 &&
      wordSimilarity(e.recommendation, lesson.recommendation) > 0.85
  );
}

function wordSimilarity(a: string, b: string): number {
  const shorter = a.length < b.length ? a : b;
  const longer = a.length >= b.length ? a : b;
  const words = shorter.toLowerCase().split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean);
  if (words.length === 0) return 0;
  const matches = words.filter((w) => longer.toLowerCase().includes(w)).length;
  return matches / words.length;
}
```

> Note: Compares `summary` + `recommendation` (not `pattern`, which doesn't exist). Case-insensitive, whitespace-normalised.

---

## Step 3 — Integration in hooks.ts (onSessionEnd only)

**Before:**
```ts
for (const lesson of lessons) {
  await writeMulchLesson(lesson, context.repoRoot);
}
```

**After:**
```ts
import { DefaultMemoryQualifier } from './qualifier/index.js';

// Load existing candidates to deduplicate against
const existingLessons = await loadExistingCandidates(context.repoRoot);
const qualifier = new DefaultMemoryQualifier(existingLessons);

for (const lesson of lessons) {
  if (qualifier.accept(lesson)) {
    await writeMulchLesson(lesson, context.repoRoot);
  }
}
```

A `loadExistingCandidates(repoRoot)` helper reads `.mulch/candidates.jsonl` and returns parsed lessons for dedup comparison.

---

## What is NOT changed

- Human review process unchanged
- `candidates.jsonl` format unchanged
- Mulch storage mechanism unchanged
- Backward compatible — no existing lesson writer needs updating

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `MulchLesson` in `agent-types` gains optional `confidence`, `frequency`, `severity` fields — all existing tests still pass
- [ ] `DefaultMemoryQualifier.accept()` rejects lessons scoring < 0.6 OR detected as duplicate OR too short
- [ ] Scorer defaults gracefully (score = 0.5 equivalent) when optional fields absent
- [ ] Dedup compares against existing `candidates.jsonl` entries at write time
- [ ] `onSessionEnd` filters through qualifier before calling `writeMulchLesson`
- [ ] Unit tests cover: accept, reject, deduplicate, score with missing fields
- [ ] All existing `agent-plugin-mulch` tests still pass

---

## Future Extensions (do NOT implement in this task)

- Embedding-based deduplication
- Ephemeral memory tier
- Event-driven lesson generation
- CLI review tooling for rejected candidates
- Attach `score` metadata to written lessons
